The Herald Sports Reporter
ZIMBABWE will renew their rivalry against Kenya when they clash in the Victoria Cup at Hartsfield in Bulawayo this weekend. The game will see two of the undefeated sides coming head-to-head. Kenya defeated Uganda 31-26 after a convincing 39-10 victory over Zambia in their opening match. Hilton Mudariki will captain the side with Jan Ferreira as the vice-captain. The Zimbabwe team in Uganda featured three debutants — Aiden Burnett, Dudlee White Sharpley and Rufaro Chikwaira. Saturday’s rugby showcase has several matches lined up as Bulawayo Metro U-20 girls’ team will face President 15-team before Milton High clash with Midlands Christian College. 